<font color="#FF0000">A PROPER RESPECT FOR POSTERS</font><br>
<tt>Sun Mar  2 17:16:10 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Prophet,<br>
     Find it very disturbing that you feel you must preserve anonymity due to persons taking direct potshots to you via e-mail.  Anyone doing so violates the spirit of these sites.  If one assumes he is 100% righteous; he is most certainly wrong about something somewhere.  None of us is perfect or has a monopoly on &quot;Truth&quot;.  I certainly know that my own knowledge is far from complete, that I have an agenda and biases which grows out of my beliefs and desires and that I can be wrong in matters great and small.  Here we are all human beings who should be trying to communicate with each other; not prosecutors before a grand jury trying to produce an endictment of someone.<br><br>
To those doing the attacks,                            SHAME!!  All you're doing is helping to destroy any good done through these sites.  For your sakes, I hope you're like Caesar's wife.  To borrow from John McCormick:  &quot;You're in my minimal high regard.&quot;  And I don't care if you know where I am or how to find me.<br><br>
